laboratory_examinations.findings: CSF showed 815 RBCs/mm3, 14 WBCs/mm3 (43% neutrophils, 38% lymphocytes, 14% monocytes, 4% other mononuclear cells, 1% eosinophils), glucose concentration of 44 mg/dL, and protein concentration of 69 mg/dL.
Blood titer of CF antibody to yeast was 1:256, and to mycelial antigen was 1:512. CSF titer of CF antibody to yeast was 1:4, and to mycelial antigen was 1:4.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Blood Urea Nitrogen Level and Serum Creatinine Level
laboratory_examinations.findings: Peak blood urea nitrogen was 107 mg/dL; serum creatinine level peaked at 5.2 mg/dL, returned to 1.3 mg/dL after Foley catheter insertion.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Serum creatinine levels initially peaked and later decreased significantly post-intervention.
